msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``3d:tessellate``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7157
msgid "Transect"
msgstr "Transetto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7158
msgid "Creates transects on vertices for (multi)linestring."
msgstr "Crea transetti sui vertici per (multi)linee."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7160
msgid ""
"A transect is a line oriented from an angle (by default perpendicular) to "
"the input polylines (at vertices)."
msgstr ""
"Un transetto è una linea orientata da un angolo (predefinito: "
"perpendicolare) ad una polilinea in ingresso (ai vertici)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7163
msgid ""
"Field(s) from feature(s) are returned in the transect with these new fields:"
msgstr ""
"Il campo(i) dell'elemento(i) sono restituiti nel transetto con questi nuovi "
"campi:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7166
msgid "TR_FID: ID of the original feature"
msgstr "TR_FID: ID dell'elemento originale"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7167
msgid "TR_ID: ID of the transect. Each transect have an unique ID"
msgstr "TR_ID: ID del transetto. Ogni transetto ha un ID univoco"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7168
msgid "TR_SEGMENT: ID of the segment of the linestring"
msgstr "TR_SEGMENT: ID del segmento della linea"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7169
msgid "TR_ANGLE: Angle in degrees from the original line at the vertex"
msgstr "TR_ANGLE: Angolo in gradi dalla linea originale al vertice"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7170
msgid "TR_LENGTH: Total length of the transect returned"
msgstr "TR_LENGTH: Lunghezza totale del transetto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7171
msgid ""
"TR_ORIENT: Side of the transect (only on the left or right of the line, or "
"both side)"
msgstr ""
"TR_ORIENT: Lato del transetto (solamente a sinistra o a destra della linea, "
"o entrambi i lati)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7180
msgid "Dashed red lines represent the transect of the input line layer"
msgstr ""
"La linea rossa tratteggiata rappresenta il transetto del vettore lineare in "
"ingresso."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7198
msgid "**Length of the transect**"
msgstr "**Lunghezza del transetto**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7203
msgid "Length in map unit of the transect"
msgstr "Lunghezza in unità di mappa del transetto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7204
msgid "**Angle in degrees from the original line at the vertices**"
msgstr "**Angolo in gradi dalla linea originale ai vertici**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7208
msgid "Default: 90.0"
msgstr "Predefinito: 90.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7209
msgid "Change the angle of the transect"
msgstr "Cambiare l'angolo del transetto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7210
msgid "**Side to create the transect**"
msgstr "**Lato per creare il transetto**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7213
msgid "Choose the side of the transect. Available options are:"
msgstr "Scegli il lato del transetto. Le opzioni disponibili sono:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7215
msgid "0 --- Left"
msgstr "0 --- Sinistro"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7216
msgid "1 --- Right"
msgstr "1 --- Destro"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7217
msgid "2 --- Both"
msgstr "2 --- Entrambi"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7219
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7243
msgid "**Transect**"
msgstr "**Transetto**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7224
msgid ""
"Specify the output line layer. :ref:`One of <output_parameter_widget>`:"
msgstr ""
"Specifica il layer della linea in uscita. :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7246
msgid "Output line layer"
msgstr "Vettore lineare in uscita "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7251
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:transect``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:transect``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7261
msgid "Translate"
msgstr "Trasla"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7262
msgid ""
"Moves the geometries within a layer, by offsetting with a predefined X and Y"
" displacement."
msgstr ""
"Sposta le geometrie di un layer, con uno spostamento di offset X e Y "
"prestabilito."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7265
msgid "Z and M values present in the geometry can also be translated."
msgstr ""
"Anche i valori Z e M presenti nella geometria possono essere traslati."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:7270
msgid ""
"Features in red represent the translated geometry of the input (blue) layer"
msgstr ""
"Elementi in rosso rappresentano la geometria traslata del layer in ingresso "
"(blu)"

